Rosneft, MGTS, Norilsk Nickel May Move: Russian Equity Preview

-- B y   H e n r y   M e y e r
-- 
2011-04-14T20:01:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-14/rosneft-mgts-norilsk-nickel-may-move-russian-equity-preview.html
The following companies may be
active in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and
share prices are from the previous close in Moscow.  The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  retreated 1.6 percent to 1,781.51.  OAO Rosneft (ROSN RX): The board of directors of state-run
Rosneft,  Russia ’s largest oil company, recommended a dividend
for 2010 of 2.76 rubles, a 20 percent increase from 2009. Shares
fell 3 percent to 244.95 rubles.  OAO  Moscow City Telephone (MGTS)  : The Russian fixed-
line operator asked shareholders to approve a payment of 197.94
rubles a preferred and common share for 2010. Shares in the
company dropped 0.6 percent to 358.34 rubles.  OAO GMK Norilsk Nickel (GMKN RX): Russia’s largest mining
company may move after copper fell in  London , capping the
longest slump in three months, on concern that demand will
decline as  China , the world’s main consumer, tightens credit
further to stem inflation. Russia’s largest producer of nickel
and copper declined 1.3 percent to 7,661 rubles on the Micex
Index.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Henry Meyer in Moscow at 
